  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN146.1-kilavi">vāyil vēṇṭic ceṉṟa <app><lem>pāṇaṟkut</lem><rdg wit="#C3">pāṇaṉukkut</rdg></app> talaimakaḷ vāyiṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How SHE refused the door to the bard who came, desirous of the door.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN146.1">
              <l>valimiku muṉpi ṉaṇṇa <supplied>ṉa</supplied>llēṟu</l>
              <l>paṉimalarp poykaip pakalcela maṟuki<anchor n="1"/></l>
              <l>maṭakka ṇerumai māṉāku kaḷīip</l>
              <l>paṭappai naṇṇiya paḻaṉat talkuṅ</l>
              <l>kalimaki ḻūra ṉolimaṇi neṭuntē</l>
              <l>roḷḷiḻai makaḷir cērip<anchor n="2"/> paṉṉā</l>
              <l>ḷiyaṅka lāṉā tāyiṉ vayaṅkiḻai</l>
              <l>yārkol laḷiyar tāmē yempō<supplied>ṉ</supplied></l>
              <l>māyap parattai vāymoḻi nampi</l>
              <l>vaḷipōt tuyalvarun<anchor n="3"/> taḷipoḻi malariṟ</l>
              <l>ṟaṇpaṉi yākat tuṟaippak kaṇpacan</l>
              <l>tāyamu mayalu maruḷat</l>
              <l>tāyōm pāynalam vēṇṭā tōrē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>The man from a village delighting in bustle, (5ab)</l>
                <l>where the majestic good bull with strength surpassing strength (1)</l>
                <l>roams the pond with dewy blossom, while the day goes, (2)</l>
                <l>exults in the dark young she-buffalo with innocent eyes (3)</l>
                <l>[and] abides in the paddy field close to the gardens, (4)</l>
                <l>since [his] long chariot with sounding bells does not stop moving,</l>
                <l>for many days, towards the quarters of bright-jewelled women, (5cd-6c)</l>
                <l>who are they, with glowing gems, pitiable ones, like us, (6df.)</l>
                <l>trusting in the words from the mouth of a deceptive courtesan, (8)</l>
                <l>who do not need [their] choice beauty [anymore], that was protected by [their] mothers, (13)</l>
                <l>so that [their] companions and the neighbourhood are confused, (12)</l>
                <l>[their] eyes paling while cool dew drips on [their] bosoms, (11)</l>
                <l>like flowers flowing with drops that come into swinging as the wind goes? (10)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

